INSERT INTO `cache_field` VALUES ('field:node:20','a:5:{s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:936:\"<p>Why are we here... starting a new church?</p><p>I believe that one of the most important things we can do, being a brand new church, is to clarify our purpose: Why are we doing this? By defining our purpose and always keeping that purpose in the forefront of everything we do, we can (hopefully) avoid the many pitfalls that get ministries side-tracked today.</p><p>Our purpose (as a church and as individuals) is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</p><ul><li>We are not here to please men; we are here to please God.</li><li>We are not here to enjoy the comforts and entertainment of the world; we are here to enjoy God.</li></ul><p>Those two things work together: When we are glorifying God we will be enjoying Him forever (the way to enjoy God is to do that which glorifies Him).</p><p>So, if you&#39;re not enjoying God... maybe you should evaluate whether or not you&#39;re living in a way that glorifies and pleases Him.</p>\";s:7:\"summary\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:935:\"<p>Why are we here... starting a new church?</p>\n<p>I believe that one of the most important things we can do, being a brand new church, is to clarify our purpose: Why are we doing this? By defining our purpose and always keeping that purpose in the forefront of everything we do, we can (hopefully) avoid the many pitfalls that get ministries side-tracked today.</p>\n<p>Our purpose (as a church and as individuals) is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</p>\n<ul><li>We are not here to please men; we are here to please God.</li>\n<li>We are not here to enjoy the comforts and entertainment of the world; we are here to enjoy God.</li>\n</ul><p>Those two things work together: When we are glorifying God we will be enjoying Him forever (the way to enjoy God is to do that which glorifies Him).</p>\n<p>So, if you\'re not enjoying God... maybe you should evaluate whether or not you\'re living in a way that glorifies and pleases Him.</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:16:\"field_audio_file\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:2:{i:0;a:11:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"16\";s:7:\"display\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"description\";s:12:\"Introduction\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"5\";s:8:\"filename\";s:28:\"110410_01a_Purpose_intro.mp3\";s:3:\"uri\";s:54:\"public://field_audio_file/110410_01a_Purpose_intro.mp3\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"audio/mpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:7:\"2301120\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1302486864\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}}i:1;a:11:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"17\";s:7:\"display\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"description\";s:7:\"Message\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"5\";s:8:\"filename\";s:21:\"110410_01_Purpose.mp3\";s:3:\"uri\";s:47:\"public://field_audio_file/110410_01_Purpose.mp3\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"audio/mpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:8:\"12384072\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1302486864\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}}}}s:21:\"field_preaching_notes\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"15\";s:7:\"display\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"description\";s:12:\"Sermon Notes\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"5\";s:8:\"filename\";s:21:\"110410_01_Purpose.pdf\";s:3:\"uri\";s:52:\"public://field_preaching_notes/110410_01_Purpose.pdf\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:15:\"application/pdf\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"125996\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1302486864\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}}}}s:12:\"field_series\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"nid\";s:2:\"27\";}}}}',0,1303758565,1),('field:node:21','a:5:{s:4:\"body\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:1623:\"<p>Discipleship: The Mission, Message #2</p><h5>Our Purpose</h5><p>Last Sunday (our first service as Harvest Baptist Church) we studied what the Bible says about our purpose. Why are we here&mdash;as individuals and as a church? Why did we start yet another church in Kansas City?</p><ul><li><strong>Our Purpose:</strong> To glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</li></ul><p>That was good place to start, but it left us with a question: How do we do that? That is our mission...</p><h5>Our Mission</h5><p>In this message we focus on what the Bible says about what we are to do in order to fulfill our life&#39;s purpose of glorifying God and enjoying Him forever.</p><ul><li><strong>Our mission:</strong> To be and make disciples of the Lord Jesus Christ.</li></ul><p>Our Mission (to be and make disciples) has two aspects: evangelism and edification.&nbsp; When we speak about discipleship, we need to get used to using these terms because they communicate a simple picture of biblical discipleship in the Church Age.</p><ul><li>Evangelism: A disciple is made, in the sense of created, through evangelism.</li><li>Edification: A disciple is made, in the sense of molded (formed), through edification.</li></ul><p>Both together (evangelism and edification) form what we call &quot;discipleship&quot; (i.e., making disciples).</p><h5>Our Church</h5><p>This is why we started Harvest Baptist Church: So that we, as individuals and as a church family, can glorify God and enjoy Him now and forever by being and making disciples of the Lord Jesus Christ. That is our purpose and that is our mission. That is what we aim to do.</p>\";s:7:\"summary\";s:319:\"Last Sunday (our first service as Harvest Baptist Church) we studied what the Bible says about our purpose. Why are we here to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.\r\n\r\nIn this message we focus on what the Bible says about what we are to do in order to fulfill our life\'s purpose of glorifying God and enjoying Him forever.\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:1615:\"<p>Discipleship: The Mission, Message #2</p>\n<h5>Our Purpose</h5>\n<p>Last Sunday (our first service as Harvest Baptist Church) we studied what the Bible says about our purpose. Why are we here—as individuals and as a church? Why did we start yet another church in Kansas City?</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Our Purpose:</strong> To glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</li>\n</ul><p>That was good place to start, but it left us with a question: How do we do that? That is our mission...</p>\n<h5>Our Mission</h5>\n<p>In this message we focus on what the Bible says about what we are to do in order to fulfill our life\'s purpose of glorifying God and enjoying Him forever.</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Our mission:</strong> To be and make disciples of the Lord Jesus Christ.</li>\n</ul><p>Our Mission (to be and make disciples) has two aspects: evangelism and edification.  When we speak about discipleship, we need to get used to using these terms because they communicate a simple picture of biblical discipleship in the Church Age.</p>\n<ul><li>Evangelism: A disciple is made, in the sense of created, through evangelism.</li>\n<li>Edification: A disciple is made, in the sense of molded (formed), through edification.</li>\n</ul><p>Both together (evangelism and edification) form what we call \"discipleship\" (i.e., making disciples).</p>\n<h5>Our Church</h5>\n<p>This is why we started Harvest Baptist Church: So that we, as individuals and as a church family, can glorify God and enjoy Him now and forever by being and making disciples of the Lord Jesus Christ. That is our purpose and that is our mission. That is what we aim to do.</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:331:\"<p>Last Sunday (our first service as Harvest Baptist Church) we studied what the Bible says about our purpose. Why are we here to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</p>\n<p>In this message we focus on what the Bible says about what we are to do in order to fulfill our life\'s purpose of glorifying God and enjoying Him forever.</p>\n\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:16:\"field_audio_file\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:11:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"28\";s:7:\"display\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"5\";s:8:\"filename\";s:21:\"110417_02_Mission.mp3\";s:3:\"uri\";s:47:\"public://field_audio_file/110417_02_