iduals) is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</p><ul><li>We are not here to please men; we are here to please God.</li><li>We are not here to enjoy the comforts and entertainment of the world; we are here to enjoy God.</li></ul><p>Those two things work together: When we are glorifying God we will be enjoying Him forever (the way to enjoy God is to do that which glorifies Him).</p><p>So, if you&#39;re not enjoying God... maybe you should evaluate whether or not you&#39;re living in a way that glorifies and pleases Him.</p>\";s:7:\"summary\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:935:\"<p>Why are we here... starting a new church?</p>\n<p>I believe that one of the most important things we can do, being a brand new church, is to clarify our purpose: Why are we doing this? By defining our purpose and always keeping that purpose in the forefront of everything we do, we can (hopefully) avoid the many pitfalls that get ministries side-tracked today.</p>\n<p>Our purpose (as a church and as individuals) is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.</p>\n<ul><li>We are not here to please men; we are here to please God.</li>\n<li>We are not here to enjoy the comforts and entertainment of the world; we are here to enjoy God.</li>\n</ul><p>Those two things work together: When we are glorifying God we will be enjoying Him forever (the way to enjoy God is to do that which glorifies Him).</p>\n<p>So, if you\'re not enjoying God... maybe you should evaluate whether or not you\'re living in a way that glorifies and pleases Him.</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:0:{}s:16:\"field_audio_file\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:2:{i:0;a:11:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"16\";s:7:\"display\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"description\";s:12:\"Introduction\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"5\";s:8:\"filename\";s:28:\"110410_01a_Purpose_intro.mp3\";s:3:\"uri\";s:54:\"public://field_audio_file/110410_01a_Purpose_intro.mp3\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"audio/mpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:7:\"2301120\";s