INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (1,'node',' seriously absolutely looking for a church that takes christianity and the bible seriously harvest baptist church is a new congregation of biblebelieving christians committed to intentional evangelism biblical discipleship expository preaching theological training and missions if you want more bible and even more bible then join us this sunday and see if harvest baptist church is the church home that god would have for you  ',1303578617),(2,'node',' i think i ve been to this church this is just hillarious and boy did the paradoy ever get it right wow enjoy  ',0),(3,'node',' test banner image ',0),(4,'node',' who we are harvest baptist is a new church in southern johnson county kansas that seeks to glorify god and enjoy him forever by being and making disciples of the lord jesus christ we believe that the need is great in our city for more biblebelieving churches dedicated to striving to align their ministries with the model given us in the new testament we reject the mancentered seekeroriented entertainmentbased focus of so many ministries today frankly we re tired of the silliness in churches and the shallowness in many pulpits we aim to be different we are striving to build a church that looks like ephesians 41116 a church dedicated to the edification of the body of christ through the perfecting of the saints being disciples of the lord jesus christ and the work of the ministry making disciples of the lord jesus christ we are dedicated to the following five things intentional evangelism biblical discipleship expository preaching theological training both biblical and applied missions both foreign and domestic are you looking for a congregation of christians who aren t perfect but who desire to take their christianity seriously check out harvest baptist church you can find out what we believe in our statement of faith and how we propose to live out our faith in our mission statement  if you d like to know more about our pastor you can visit this page  greg kedrovsky  we would love to meet you and get to know you so please visit us this sunday  ',0),(8,'node',' where we meet location   hampton inn olathe 12081 strang line road olathe kansas 66062 time  1000 am view larger map ',0),(9,'node',' ministries children  hbc believes children are a blessing from god and we re fully committed to helping equip parents in training up their children our service is family style where children stay with their parents there is a nursery for babies through toddlers as needed  ',1303578774),(11,'node',' leadership pastor greg kedrovsky greg was ordained by and sent out from the kansas city baptist temple in august of 1995 he and his wife sue began their ministry by spending approximately two years in bogotá colombia where they learned the language and culture under the ministry of la biblia dice church god then opened the door for them to move to san josé costa rica and minister at emanuel baptist church after five years at emanuel developing bible institute curriculum and building the discipleship ministry god led them to start eastside church on the opposite side of town in march of 2002 in december 2010 at the request of their sending church greg and his family returned from the mission field greg left eastside church in the very gifted and capable hands of three pastors and several more leaders all of which were trained for the ministry at eastside greg still confident that god wants to use him in fulltime vocational ministry as a pastorteacher started harvest baptist church in southern johnson county kansas on april 10 2011 greg is a former marine and he has a bsba in accounting from central missouri state univerity and an ma in biblical and theological studies from luther rice seminary he is currently completing his master of divinity with languages at columbia evangelical seminary distance study in preparation for a doctorate in theology systematic theology and apologetics greg and sue have been married since 1991 and have three children alex kevin and rebeka  greg kedrovsky  ',1303605392),(12,'node',' contact us have a question or just want to shoot us a message use the form below name email address message  ',0),(13,'node',' statement of faith this statement is a declaration of our beliefs in areas of doctrine which we consider to be important if not essential this document is not meant to be an exhaustive theological apologetic for each topic listed below therefore we have simply tried to provide a credal statement with an adequate biblical explanation of why we believe what we believe the topics listed below are not in any specific order and the order in which they appear should in no way be construed as an ascending or descending order of magnitude or importance i scripture we believe that all the holy scriptures both old and new testaments the 66 books of the bible without apocrypha were given by the inspiration of god verbally and plenary in the original manuscripts 1cor 210 we believe that god superintended the writing of scripture by moving men to write the exact words he desired to communicate to man yet without superseding the personalities of the human authors 2pet 12021 we believe that god promised to preserve the inspired words of scripture ps 1267 we believe that scripture is the inspired word and words of god 2tim 31617 we believe it is reasonable that what god inspired he also preserved mat 2435 because god has preserved his inspired scripture we believe inspired scripture can be held in one s hand and read mat 2142 mar 1210 acts 83235 inspired scripture can be ignored and therefore can be known mat 2229 mar 1224 inspired scripture can be searched examined studied investigated john 539 acts 1711 inspired scripture can opened explained and taught systematically acts 173 1828 therefore we believe that just as the copies and possibly translations of the first century were scripture the inspired word and words of god 2tim 31517 so inspired scripture exists today in copies and translations because god promised to preserve the words he inspired we believe the scriptures today are just as inspired perfect and inerrant without contradiction the very words god desires to communicate to man as when god inspired the original manuscripts even though they have been copied transmitted and translated down through the centuries because god has both inspired and preserved the holy scriptures we accept said scriptures as our final authority we believe that the holy scripture in the english language is the king james bible also referred to as the authorized version and we therefore accept the king james bible as the perfect and infallible word and words of god our final authority ii dispensations we believe that the bible is to be carefully and studiously interpreted according to its own internal system of dispensations we believe the bible to be understood in its right context must be rightly divided by noting doctrinal differences that exist between the various ages during which god has worked 2tim 215 we believe in a biblical system of dispensations similar to that of ci scofield and lewis sperry chafer moderate dispensationalism we reject the errors of the hyperdispensationalists who over divide scripture and who refuse to acknowledge the overlap which commonly occurs when history moves from one dispensation into the next we believe that moderate dispensationalism is the only way to legitimately interpret the scripture and explain the many supposed discrepancies and contradictions in the bible which if not understood in their dispensational context lead to a mixture of truth and error and which often lead god s people into bad doctrine iii god we believe in the trinity one god who is three distinct persons the father the son the lord jesus christ and the holy spirit 1john 57 matthew 31617 2819  iv jesus christ the son of god we believe jesus christ is 100 man and 100 god commonly referred to as the hypostatic union of the two natures human and divine jesus is god in the flesh 1tim 316 we believe that jesus christ was supernaturally conceived by the holy spirit luke 135 born of the virgin mary and thus received his human body isa 714 we believe that jesus christ was in all points tempted like as we are are yet he never sinned not in thought word or in deed heb 415 we believe that jesus christ gave himself to be crucified to suffer the wrath of god on the cross and to die in our place and stead he thus became the unique innocent penal substitute and propitiation for the sins of all men and women rom 325 51221 1jn 22 we believe that jesus christ rose from the dead literally and physically after three days in the tomb and that he appeared to over 500 eyewitnesses during the 40 days after his resurrection 1cor 1536 we believe that jesus christ is now seated on the right hand of the father in heaven awaiting his return for the rapture of the church and his ultimate revelation in the second coming when he comes back to this earth to establish his 1000year reign called the millennium col 31 1thess 41318 rev 1911206  v holy spirit we believe that the holy spirit is god and that he is as much a person as the father and the lord jesus christ the holy spirit is not simply a spiritual force he is the lord 1cor 316 2cor 317 we believe that during the present age the holy spirit dwells in all true believers 1cor 1213 and that he regenerates them titus 35 giving them new spiritual life at the moment of their conversion to christ john 338 the holy spirit seals believers eph 11314 guarantees their salvation eph 430 teaches them the scriptures 1cor 213 john 1426 comforts them through the scriptures john 167 1215 guides them in life decisions by means of the scriptures 2tim 31545 and thus uses the scriptures to conform all believers to the image of christ commonly referred to as sanctification rom 829 gal 419 gal 52223 we believe that the holy spirit gives to all bornagain believers gifts and abilities that enable them to do the work to which god has called them 1cor 1214 however we also believe that the five sign gifts or signs of an apostle 2cor 1212 the gifts of tongues healing casting out devils taking up serpents and drinking deadly things without harm were given specifically by god for the confirmation of the new testament mark 161520 upon the completion of the canon of scripture after the age of the apostles around ad 100 those miraculous sign gifts ceased we believe the manifestations of these gifts today are counterfeits they are fleshly carnal and in some cases demonic 2tim 38  vi satan we believe satan the devil is a real historical being that once was a cherub ezek 2816 who fell in sin because of pride isa 141214 when satan fell he rebelled against god with onethird of the angels of heaven who are not referred to as devils or demons rev 124 we believe that satan was defeated by the lord jesus christ through his work on the cross and in his subsequent resurrection heb 214 we believe that satan still exists and that he lives and moves in the world today trying with the aid of his devils to thwart the plans of god 1thes 218 we believe one of satan s primary fields of activity is that of religion a counterfeit form of christianity 2cor 111215 we believe that satan s primary strategy among god s people is to cause them to question the certainty of the words of truth the word and words of god and to thereby lead them to usurp the final authority of god s word and words with their own personal opinions and decisions gen 31 we believe satan s final destiny will be the lake of fire rev 2010  vii genesis we believe that the story of creation in the first chapters of the book of genesis is fact and not allegory it is true history not a fable we believe in a young earth an earth that is probably no more than 8000 years old we believe that adam and eve were real historic people who were created directly by a unique act of god adam chose to sin by his own freewill that god had given him and and by so doing brought death destruction judgment and condemnation upon all his descendants upon all mankind rom 512 623  viii salvation we believe that salvation in this age the church age is by grace through faith in the finished work of the lord jesus christ on the cross and in the resurrection not by any works of merit that man could do eph 289 we believe that believing on jesus christ for salvation includes both repentance a turning from sin luke 133 5 rom 256 and faith a turning to christ in total dependence on and trust in him for salvation rom 32122 without both repentance and faith there is no salvation because there is no conversion acts 202021 1thes 19 god will save those who turn from sin to him in faith it is not the conversion of the sinner that saves him but rather the conversion of the sinner places him at the mercy of god who based on the work of the lord jesus christ will forgive the sinner of his sins and regenerate him by the spirit we believe that sinful natural man is totally depraved rom 31018 and yet able in his unregenerate state to respond to god s call to repentance and faith when confronted biblically with the gospel of the lord jesus christ rom 10917 we believe in an unlimited atonement meaning that jesus christ died for all sinners not just the elect or predestined which are terms often misunderstood and misapplied 1jn 22 we believe that god desires that all men be saved 1tim 234 through repentance and faith in christ 2pet 39 and because of that desire he is working in all sinners everywhere to bring them to saving faith in christ john 1232 168 we believe that many sinners resist the grace of god given them through the working of the holy spirit and the preaching of the gospel acts 751 thus believing we reject the reformed theology of john calvin and calvinism as it relates to soteriology the theology of salvation and the ordo salutis the order of salvation john 316 we believe that a bornagain believer is eternally secure in his salvation he did nothing to earn his salvation christ did it all and therefore he can do nothing to lose it christ does it all this eternally secure condition of the saved sinner in the present age is secured by the numerous irreversible promises of god and works of the holy spirit rom 83139 we believe that genuine salvation will normally be evidenced by a changed lifestyle a lifestyle of holiness of growing in spiritual maturity and becoming more and more like jesus christ in both character and conduct gal 419 52223 rom 829 if such evidence spiritual growth and maturity is not visible in the life of a professed believer we believe it is healthy for that person to examine his salvation to be sure that he is in the faith mat 71323 1cor 1512 2cor 135 we believe that god s principal method of saving sinners is through the preaching of the message of the cross the gospel 1cor 118 21 rom 101317 therefore we believe in the intentional active and vigorous pursuit of lost sinners through efforts such as personal witnessing openair preaching literature distribution doortodoor witnessing and any other reasonable and appropriate method of communicating the message of the gospel to the lost mat 281920 2cor 51821 we believe that biblical evangelism must include the lawful use of god s moral law to bring about a knowledge of sin and a fear of god and judgment before the good news of the gospel is presented 1tim 1811  ix the church we believe in the universal and invisible church eph 36 21 which is the body eph 12223 and bride of christ eph 52333 2cor 1123 rev 197 219 and into which the sinner is placed at the moment of his salvation 1cor 1213 all bornagain believers since acts 2 and until the rapture of the church form part of this church the body and bride of christ although all true bornagain believers form part of the universal church great majority of references to church in the new testament are to local assemblies acts 1423 we believe that in this present age all believers are expected by the lord to congregate weekly upon the first day of the week sunday with other believers in a local assembly a local church 1cor 1612 heb 102425 the local church has been given the authority to administer the two ordinances give by the lord namely baptism mat 281920 acts 1633 and the lord s supper 1cor 111734 the local church is also god s ordained structure by and through which he is carrying out his plan in the present age to evangelize the lost and edify the believers eph 41116 we believe in the ordinance of believers baptism that believers should be immersed in water as their first step of obedience after salvation acts 83538 we do not believe in pedobaptism the baptism of infants and young children but rather in credobaptism the baptism of believers therefore we believe it is biblical to baptize only those who have shown sufficient maturity to be able to discern good from evil to understand the gravity of their sinful state before a holy god to repent of their sins and to turn to christ only for salvation we believe in the ordinance of the lord s supper which is a memorial and not a means of grace 1cor 112034  x the rapture and second coming we believe in the pretribulation rapture of the church all the saints from acts 2 until the moment of the rapture 1cor 155158 1thes 41318 and in the premillennial posttribulation return of the lord jesus christ to this earth to establish his kingdom and rule among men for onethousand years rev 1911206  xi eternity we believe that all men are eternal beings having a beginning conception in the womb and yet having no end all men therefore will spend all of eternity either with christ or separated from him we believe that lost sinners that die go immediately to hell a place of conscious torment in flames luke 16161931 where they wait until the day of their final judgment they will be brought up from hell judged by god for every thought word and deed and then cast for all eternity into the lake of fire where their torment will never cease rev 201115 218 we believe that those sinners that god has saved will live with him for all eternity in a new creation which will be free of sin suffering and death rev 211 2215   statement faith  ',0),(14,'node',' mission our mission is simple to be and make disciples of the lord jesus christ we intend on accomplishing our mission through five key areas intentional evangelism biblical discipleship expository preaching theological training missions  mission statement  ',0),(15,'node',' unicorns in the bible are there unicorns in the bible why of course there are  wretched bites ',0),(19,'node',' first service  the first service was awesome we had 27 in attendance include a family of visitors it was very encouraging to see everyone there and to get started on our first preaching series here s a picture so if for no other reason we can say we started this thing in a guy s basement  ',1303605471),(20,'node',' our purpose why are we here  why are we here starting a new church i believe that one of the most important things we can do being a brand new church is to clarify our purpose why are we doing this by defining our purpose and always keeping that purpose in the forefront of everything we do we can hopefully avoid the many pitfalls that get ministries sidetracked today our purpose as a church and as individuals is to glorify god and enjoy him forever we are not here to please men we are here to please god we are not here to enjoy the comforts and entertainment of the world we are here to enjoy god those two things work together when we are glorifying god we will be enjoying him forever the way to enjoy god is to do that which glorifies him so if you re not enjoying god maybe you should evaluate whether or not you re living in a way that glorifies and pleases him sermon notes introduction message ',1303689551),(21,'node',' our mission be and make disciples  discipleship the mission message 2 our purpose last